From: Armbian
Subject: orangepi-win: USB1 VBUS (PD7) + USB host + SPL SPI

Rebased onto v2026.07-rc4's orangepi_win_defconfig (carried from the v2024.01-era
fix-usb1-vbus-opiwin patch). Drives the USB host VBUS GPIO (PD7) and enables
USB host + SPL SPI-flash boot. The old patch's DT half (reg_usb1_vbus) is dropped:
Linux powers USB via its own dtb, and u-boot driving PD7 high carries the VBUS
state into the kernel anyway. None of these are in the upstream defconfig.

--- a/configs/orangepi_win_defconfig
+++ b/configs/orangepi_win_defconfig
@@ -12,3 +12,6 @@
 CONFIG_SPI=y
 CONFIG_USB_EHCI_HCD=y
 CONFIG_USB_OHCI_HCD=y
+CONFIG_SPL_SPI_FLASH_SUPPORT=y
+CONFIG_USB1_VBUS_PIN="PD7"
+CONFIG_USB_HOST=y
